docs.abstract: Tom Steyer, the liberal billionaire who has crusaded for impeaching President Trump, is pouring money into electing Andrew Gillum governor of Florida.
docs.snippet: Tom Steyer, the liberal billionaire who has crusaded for impeaching President Trump, is pouring money into electing Andrew Gillum governor of Florida.
docs.lead_paragraph: Tom Steyer, the billionaire investor and Democratic activist, has directed his political operation to spend more than $5 million aiding Andrew Gillum’s campaign for governor of Florida, an enormous investment that will test whether fired-up Democratic voters can flip control of a state long dominated by Republicans.

headline.main: Tom Steyer to Spend Millions Backing Andrew Gillum in Florida

docs.abstract: The Mississippi governor’s choice to fill the seat of retiring Senator Thad Cochran may give an insurgent conservative an opening — and Democrats a chance.
docs.snippet: The Mississippi governor’s choice to fill the seat of retiring Senator Thad Cochran may give an insurgent conservative an opening — and Democrats a chance.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Phil Bryant, the Republican governor of Mississippi, defied a last-minute appeal from the White House and announced Wednesday that he was appointing Cindy Hyde-Smith, the state’s agricultural commissioner, to fill the seat Senator Thad Cochran is vacating next month.

headline.main: Mississippi Governor Defies White House With His G.O.P. Appointee to Senate
headline.print_headline: Woman in Congress: A First for Mississippi

byline.original: By Jonathan Martin and Alan Blinder

docs.abstract: Party leaders are cautioning candidates in the midterm elections not to campaign on impeachment, for fear of inciting conservatives to vote in defense of President Trump.
docs.snippet: Party leaders are cautioning candidates in the midterm elections not to campaign on impeachment, for fear of inciting conservatives to vote in defense of President Trump.
docs.lead_paragraph: MATTHEWS, N.C. — Democrats in Washington are wary of any talk about impeaching President Trump, but in this swing district in North Carolina, Janis Silverman is feeling no such constraints. A 72-year-old retired teacher, Ms. Silverman wrote to her congressman Tuesday to demand the House start impeachment proceedings.

headline.main: Democratic Split on Impeachment Talk: Officials Avoid It, but Voters Are Eager for It
headline.print_headline: ‘Impeachment’? Democrats Split On Use of Word

docs.abstract: A county in New Jersey sent out “a large percentage” of mail ballots with erroneous address information. The county clerk said it would accept all ballots.

docs.lead_paragraph: There were two unusual lines, both confusing and concerning, on Jonathan Latimer’s vote-by-mail ballot: "MAIL 6619” and “BROWN UNIVERSITY.”

headline.main: Thousands of Voters Received Ballots With Errors. (But They’ll Still Count.)

docs.abstract: Amid fried catfish and sweet tea, two friends in Mississippi, who agree on next to nothing about politics, navigate their differences as part of their daily shifts.
docs.snippet: Amid fried catfish and sweet tea, two friends in Mississippi, who agree on next to nothing about politics, navigate their differences as part of their daily shifts.
docs.lead_paragraph: SOUTHAVEN, Miss. — Crystal Walls and Lovetta Green have the easy warmth that comes with working together 23 years, Ms. Walls as a waitress and Ms. Green in the kitchen of the restaurant where everyone in town seems to gather.

headline.main: In a Mississippi Restaurant, Two Americas Coexist Side by Side
headline.print_headline: Friends for Years, Side by Side, But They Can’t Agree on Trump

docs.lead_paragraph: MAZOMANIE, Wis. — The most memorable part of Scott Walker’s run for president in 2016 was how he ended it: By dissing Donald J. Trump, his chief rival in a crowded race.

docs.abstract: Mr. Cruz, the Texas Republican senator, will try to use the face-off to widen his lead in the polls, while Mr. O’Rourke, the Democratic congressman challenging him, is hoping to recapture momentum.
docs.snippet: Mr. Cruz, the Texas Republican senator, will try to use the face-off to widen his lead in the polls, while Mr. O’Rourke, the Democratic congressman challenging him, is hoping to recapture momentum.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN ANTONIO — Representative Beto O’Rourke of Texas, who has fallen behind Senator Ted Cruz in the polls in their hotly contested Senate race, turned sharply aggressive in their second debate on Tuesday night as he attacked Mr. Cruz’s honesty and character while the two clashed over abortion, climate change and other red-versus-blue divides.

headline.main: Beto O’Rourke Attacks Ted Cruz as ‘Dishonest’ in Debate in Senate Race

docs.abstract: Robert Pittenger, seeking his fourth term, lost a primary challenge on Tuesday to Mark Harris, a Baptist minister who opposes same-sex marriage.
docs.snippet: Robert Pittenger, seeking his fourth term, lost a primary challenge on Tuesday to Mark Harris, a Baptist minister who opposes same-sex marriage.
docs.lead_paragraph: He is a Baptist minister who opposes gay marriage, a Republican who is critical of his party’s leaders in Congress, and a candidate who ran a shoestring campaign against a House incumbent. And on Wednesday, Mark Harris found himself in another role: A giant-killer of the 2018 midterm elections.

headline.main: North Carolina Republican Is First Incumbent Ousted in 2018
headline.print_headline: North Carolina Republican Is First Incumbent to Lose

docs.abstract: The key races in the state, which President Trump won by 26 points in 2016, are for the governorship and the Senate seat being vacated by Bob Corker.
docs.snippet: The key races in the state, which President Trump won by 26 points in 2016, are for the governorship and the Senate seat being vacated by Bob Corker.
docs.lead_paragraph: Tennessee primary voters on Thursday will choose which candidates to send to the general election. Democrats hope that the governorship and a Senate seat may be up for grabs, and the state, which President Trump won by 26 points in 2016, also has three open House seats.

headline.main: Tennessee Primaries: What to Watch For
